summary:
Target Achievement(s): Improvement in the Fight against Corruption; Free and Fairer Elections; and Protection of Fundamentals of Human Rights

Legistlative Interest(s): Anti-Corruption, Electoral Reforms, Human Rights

Awards & Honours: Life Member, University of Abuja Student Union Government, FCT - 2000;
World Peace Ambassador - 2008;
Icon of Hope, Afro Caribbean Society,  University, Reading, UK - 2010;
Balewa Award for Young Achievers - 2010;
Paul Harris Fellow Rotary International Award- 2011

Target Achievement(s): To be an outstanding Legislator in the 7th Session of the National Assembly

Legistlative Interest(s): Legislative development pf the Health sector, Education with regards to the female child, Women Empowerment and Maternal protection.

Awards & Honours: SATBILA Award for 'The Most Outstanding Legislator', 2010;
Selfless Service Award by NEPU-PRP Commitee, 2008;
Northern Nigeria Women Merit Award, 2007;
Rotary Club Award, 2006;
Distinguished Leadership Award, 2006

Target Achievement(s): 1. Motion on the Mandatory Installation of the Emergency Locator Transmitter Beacon 406MHz in all Aircraft:
Impact: This motion led to the resolution by the Senate to mandate Committee on Aviation to commence investigation of the non-installation of Locator Beacons 406MHz in Aircraft, several revelations have been made by the Committee which will aid the implementation of the installation of Emergency Locator Transmitter Beacons 406MHz on all aircraft flying in Nigeria which will in turn improve air safety in country.
ii. Establishment of Mining Cadastre Office, Bill 2008
Impact: This Bill even though withdrawn due to some technical details helped to create awareness and bring to the front burner the immediate need for the establishment of the Mining Cadastre Office, as provided by the Minerals and Mining Act 2007.
iii. Motion on Unauthorized Expenditure and Misapplication of Funds from the Development of Natural Resources Fund.
Impact: This motion led to the Senate Resolution mandating the Committee to commence investigation of unauthorized expenditure misapplication of funds from the Development of Natural Resources Fund, some serious revelations have been made and further expenditure from the fund put on hold.
iv. Chaired and facilitated the hosting of the First National Summit on Solid Minerals at Jos, Plateau State; Titled, Nigeria: An Emerging Solid Minerals Economy.
Impact: The summit helped to create awareness as to the potential of Solid Minerals as an alternative source of foreign exchange earner for the country and a means of alleviating poverty and offering gainful employment to the teeming unemployed Nigerians.
v. First Stakeholders Forum in Rivers East Senatorial District:
Impact: Created a forum for interaction and enlightenment of my constituent as well created the opportunity to feel the pulse of the electorates in the senatorial district. Bursaries were awarded to over 100 Students and over 260 Widows received immediate poverty alleviation funds to start up small scale businesses. This forum is unprecedented in the history of Senatorial Representation in Rivers East Senatorial District.
vi. Co-Sponsored several Bills and Motions:
Impact: My Incisive and well researched contributions to these Bill and Motion have helped to uplift the standard of debate in the Senate.

Legistlative Interest(s): Niger Delta And Making Laws Relating To marine Environment For The Benefit Of The Riverine Dwellers Of The Country.

